F1 Top Teams Plan Germany Meeting on Sport’s Future, Sky Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-04T19:44:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/f1-top-teams-plan-germany-meeting-on-sport-s-future-sky-says.html
Formula One’s top teams Ferrari,
McLaren, Mercedes and Red Bull Racing will meet in Stuttgart,
 Germany  on May 14 to discuss the ownership of the sport, a new
commercial rights agreement and other technical sporting issues,
Sky News reported on its  website , without saying where it got
the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 